[~hspencer], the euca2ools region option is used with the local euca2ools configuration to determine which endpoint to use. Each region (endpoint) will return only availability zones for that region (as per AWS/EC2):

{quote}
Describes one or more of the Availability Zones that are available to you. The results include zones only for the region you're currently using. If there is an event impacting an Availability Zone, you can use this request to view the state and any provided message for that Availability Zone.
{quote}

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/API_DescribeAvailabilityZones.html

